metadata.name: Great Terrible №1
metadata.description:
The images generated by the neural network are truly beautiful, and at the same time terrifying when the phenomenon of pareidolia comes into force: 
Pareidolia is a kind of visual illusions (the so—called "sensory illusions") that we have from our distant ancestors. Thus, a vague and indistinct visual image is perceived as something distinct and definite - for example, figures of people, animals or fabulous creatures! 
What do you see in this picture?
